test 在英語-中文（繁體）詞典中的翻譯

test
noun [ C ]
uk
/test/ us
/test/
Add to word list
A1
a way of discovering, by questions or practical activities, what someone knows, or what someone or something can do or is like
測驗，考查
The class are doing/having a spelling test today. 今天班裡有一個拼寫測驗。
She had to take/do an aptitude test before she got the job. 她先接受了能力測試後才得到這份工作。
B1
a medical examination of part of your body in order to find out how healthy it is or what is happening with it
（體格）檢查;化驗
a blood/urine test 驗血／尿檢
an eye test 視力檢查
a pregnancy test 妊娠檢查
The doctors have done some tests to try and find out what's wrong with her. 醫生做了一些檢查，想查出她的問題出在哪裡。
an act of using something to find out if it is working correctly or how effective it is
試驗
The new missiles are currently undergoing tests. 新導彈目前正在進行試驗。
B2
a situation that shows how good something is
檢驗；考驗
Driving on that icy road was a real test of my skill. 在那條結了冰的路上駕車是對我駕駛技術的一次真正考驗。
a test match
（板球，橄欖球等的）國際錦標賽（同 test match）
Australia won the test by 197 runs. 澳大利亞以197分贏得了這次錦標賽。
更多範例减少例句
  • We're revising algebra for the test tomorrow.
  • She scored 18 out of 20 in the spelling test.
  • She's been trying to pass her driving test for six years and she's finally succeeded.
  • The medical tests showed some variation in the baby's heart rate.
  • Candidates who are successful in the written test will be invited for an interview.

習語

put something to the test
test
verb
uk
/test/ us
/test/
B2 [ T ]
to put something through a process in order to discover if it is safe, works correctly, etc., or if something is present in it
試驗；檢驗；試用；檢測
The manufacturers are currently testing the new engine. 生產廠家目前正試驗這種新的引擎。
They tested her blood for signs of the infection. 他們驗了她的血，看看是否有感染的跡象。
[ T ]
to do a medical examination of part of someone's body or of a particular physical ability
檢查（身體）
This exercise tests your reflexes.
I had my eyes tested.
B1 [ T ]
to give someone a set of questions, in order to measure their knowledge or ability
測驗，測試;考查;考試
Will you test me on the chemistry I've been learning? 你要考一考我一直在學的化學嗎？
Pupils are tested every half-term.
B2 [ T ]
If a situation tests someone, it proves how good, strong, etc. they are.
考驗
You will face a series of physical challenges that will test even the fittest and most determined.
That lecture really tested my powers of endurance, it was so boring. 那個講座簡直是在考驗我的忍耐力，實在太枯燥了。
